## What to do next
At this stage you need to design a plan for rescaling the regression targets in order to obtain the best performance.
This plan can be based on the distribution and scale of the targets, on the metric that is considered in this competition, and on the fact that a deep learning model will be used to make the predictions.

To rescale the targets, you have to create a class called TabRegressionTargetScaler and implement 4 methods:
    - __init__: can contain auxiliary attributes used in `fit`
    - fit: will be called on the training regression targets DataFrame
    - transform: to transform the regression targets after the fit.
    - inverse_transform: to map the test predictions back to the original scales.

This class can even simply be a wrapper of sklearn's transforms classes, or it can implement a trivial transformation that do not modify the data if no rescaling is deemed necessary.

